1
00:01:29,270 --> 00:01:34,910
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:37,770
[Episode 24]

3
00:01:39,479 --> 00:01:41,070
Why are we at Anning Hospital?

4
00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:45,310
[Tiecheng Anning Hospital]

5
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:43,160
Sick people need treatment.

6
00:01:46,509 --> 00:01:47,310
Alright then.

7
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:49,720
I'll arrange a one-month stay for him.

8
00:01:49,789 --> 00:01:51,950
Don't let him out until he's cured.

9
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:54,120
So he won't cause trouble outside.

10
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,120
I think you should

11
00:01:55,229 --> 00:01:56,630
just hurry up and retire.

12
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,039
What are you doing

13
00:01:58,039 --> 00:01:59,210
every day?

14
00:01:59,580 --> 00:02:00,990
Does this have anything to do
with solving cases?

15
00:02:00,990 --> 00:02:02,160
Stop nagging.

16
00:02:02,710 --> 00:02:04,310
I won't retire even if you do.

17
00:02:06,870 --> 00:02:07,430
Alright.

18
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:09,590
Stay here

19
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,380
and focus on recovery.

20
00:02:14,470 --> 00:02:16,470
Come on, change into these clothes.

21
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,240
What's wrong?

22
00:02:35,380 --> 00:02:36,360
Don't be nervous.

23
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,290
That's the bell for the noon break.

24
00:02:39,710 --> 00:02:40,570
Zhang Xiaoman?

25
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:42,420
Let's go.

26
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,000
We run a very regular schedule here.

27
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,520
You should get up at 6:00

28
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:50,400
every morning

29
00:02:50,850 --> 00:02:52,590
and go to bed at 8:00 in the evening.

30
00:02:52,590 --> 00:02:55,470
At noon, there's a one-hour nap break.

31
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:58,470
You don't have to sleep if you can't,

32
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:01,030
but you must not disturb others.

33
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:01,750
Got it?

34
00:03:05,550 --> 00:03:06,180
Let's go.

35
00:03:11,110 --> 00:03:14,040
Your world ends here, Zhang Xiaoman.

36
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:16,000
[Inpatient Ward]

37
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:20,000
This big iron gate is

38
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:21,520
usually locked.

39
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,360
You can't go out at will.

40
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,200
Understand?

41
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,310
It's dangerous.

42
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:26,240
Get in.

43
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,210
Stand there and wait for me.

44
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:33,980
Good. Let's go.

45
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,700
This room, Zhang Xiaoman.

46
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,310
You rest in this room.

47
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:45,680
Call me if you need anything.

48
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:46,970
My name is Qian Juan.

49
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,120
Got it?

50
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:51,280
Go on in.

51
00:04:21,990 --> 00:04:23,960
Why was that boy, Xiaoman...

52
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:26,870
Why w-was he s-sent

53
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:29,010
to the Anning Hospital?

54
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:30,240
You startled me,

55
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,120
seriously.

56
00:04:32,070 --> 00:04:34,730
Didn't you notice it
when he came home last time?

57
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,800
I did.

58
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:41,070
He just blurted things out

59
00:04:41,310 --> 00:04:42,170
all of a sudden.

60
00:04:43,130 --> 00:04:45,120
Sometimes I didn't know
who he was talking to.

61
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,650
Why didn't you tell me then?

62
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:49,190
I didn't find a chance to tell you,

63
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:51,260
with all the trouble you caused.

64
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:52,909
Cut the crap.

65
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,510
Look at us.

66
00:05:00,390 --> 00:05:02,720
We never had any children our whole lives.

67
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:05,560
We treat him as our own son.

68
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:12,430
How did he end up in Anning Hospital?

69
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,800
This may not necessarily be a bad thing.

70
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,160
Reimbursement is difficult
to get these days.

71
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:28,020
It's good to get it done d-directly
at the hospital.

72
00:05:30,970 --> 00:05:31,950
I have to go see him

73
00:05:31,950 --> 00:05:33,159
and make him a few dishes.

74
00:05:33,159 --> 00:05:34,270
What dishes?

75
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:35,830
Go ask Xia Lei's mother.

76
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:36,960
What... What a mess.

77
00:05:37,310 --> 00:05:38,510
I'll go get some meat.

78
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:40,510
Does the hospital allow us
to send meat?

79
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:41,120
J-Just make it.

80
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,040
Meat is undoubtedly n-nourishing.

81
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:43,800
Forget about those beans.

82
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,000
J-Just stew the meat.

83
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:03,090
Zhang Xiaoman, someone's here
to visit you.

84
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:06,600
Sir,

85
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,750
make it quick.

86
00:06:27,230 --> 00:06:30,430
Now I'm old, and I'm still
causing trouble for you, my boy.

87
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:34,480
Mr. Ding.

88
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,280
I brought you some good food.

89
00:06:42,330 --> 00:06:44,130
Sausage. Freshly made.

90
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,040
I already ate.

91
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,240
You ate?

92
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,240
I was eating

93
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,190
and on medication.

94
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:57,470
Once I took the pills,

95
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:01,270
I got dizzy and happy.

96
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:03,070
How could medicine make you happy?

97
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:06,000
Could that...
Could that possibly be good medicine?

98
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:09,040
I made this especially for you.

99
00:07:09,510 --> 00:07:10,430
Eat up.

100
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,480
Let me know what you like,

101
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:13,280
and I'll make it again next time.

102
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,000
I won't grill chicken ribs anymore.

103
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:17,680
They just bring about trouble.

104
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,540
Never grill them again in my life.

105
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:22,880
But if you want, I'll grill them for you.

106
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:27,830
Xiaoman.

107
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:29,920
Xiaoman?

108
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:30,920
Xiaoman, don't scare me.

109
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,920
X-Xiaoman?

110
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:32,920
Xiaoman!

111
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:35,310
Doctor! Doctor!

112
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:37,510
Keep it down, sir.

113
00:07:37,510 --> 00:07:38,070
What happened?

114
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:39,240
He just collapsed!

115
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:41,120
He just took his medicine.

116
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,240
It's kicking in.

117
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:42,840
He's fine.

118
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:44,000
So, what do we do now?

119
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,260
Just help him into bed.

120
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,760
-Take it slow.
-He's big.

121
00:07:49,690 --> 00:07:50,310
Oh, my God.

122
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,510
Let me do it. Leave it to me.

123
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:51,830
You might

124
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:52,800
b-break his back this way.

125
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,680
Be careful.

126
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,270
Are you sure he's okay?

127
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:02,430
He's fine. Don't worry.

128
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:03,720
Doesn't he need an X-ray or something?

129
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,720
No need. Look, he's snoring already.

130
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,120
It's okay. Rest assured.

131
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:09,280
Call me if you need anything.

132
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,430
Mr. Ding,

133
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,909
I bought you the Beijing Erguotou.

134
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:36,429
Here is your tea, Mentor.

135
00:08:36,870 --> 00:08:38,549
Mr. Ding, you make me do farm work.

136
00:08:38,549 --> 00:08:39,880
Am I a worker or a farmer?

137
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,390
With my mentor's skills,

138
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:44,650
he'd wipe them all out.

139
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:46,080
Mr. Ding,

140
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,450
I eat and drink at your place every day—

141
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:50,880
what's wrong with me
giving you some money?

142
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:09,550
Xiaoman,

143
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:11,120
Dad is leaving.

144
00:09:11,510 --> 00:09:13,910
I don't want to be trapped here
my whole life.

145
00:09:13,910 --> 00:09:14,730
Xiaoman.

146
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,360
You don't need to bring so many things

147
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,840
to my place.

148
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,240
It's too big this year,

149
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:21,270
but it'll fit perfectly in a year or two.

150
00:09:21,270 --> 00:09:22,930
Why is your dance hall closed?

151
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,630
No one dances anymore.

152
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,790
No more motorcycle-riding.
It's closed, out of business.

153
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:29,320
Xiaoman!

154
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:30,670
Grandma!

155
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:31,790
Don't leave me!

156
00:09:31,790 --> 00:09:33,510
Aren't we waiting for my dad to come back?

157
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:35,510
What about my dad? Will he come back?

158
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:38,750
Xiaoman, go home.

159
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,360
Well, Xiaoman

160
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:04,130
really has suffered a lot.

161
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:07,150
How did he end up at Anning Hospital?

162
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,720
Young people are
under so much pressure nowadays.

163
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,960
More and more of them are
having mental health issues.

164
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:14,840
It really is.

165
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,870
I need to call Xia Lei.

166
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:20,600
Right.

167
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:22,680
Talk to him about it.

168
00:10:32,630 --> 00:10:33,890
Hello? Mom, what's up?

169
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,270
I'm telling you something,

170
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:36,400
but don't be scared.

171
00:10:37,030 --> 00:10:38,360
I'm not a child anymore.

172
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,480
What could possibly scare me?

173
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,320
Well, Xiaoman...

174
00:10:44,270 --> 00:10:46,630
He was diagnosed
with auditory hallucinations.

175
00:10:46,630 --> 00:10:48,690
He's staying at Anning Hospital now.

176
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:52,040
Why was he hospitalized all of a sudden?

177
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,690
How about this? I...

178
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:54,740
I'll find time

179
00:10:54,740 --> 00:10:55,670
to go back.

180
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:56,390
I'll ask for leave.

181
00:10:56,390 --> 00:10:57,270
No, no. Don't

182
00:10:57,270 --> 00:10:58,360
worry about it for now.

183
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,480
J-Just rest assured.

184
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:00,550
Your dad and I are here,

185
00:11:00,550 --> 00:11:01,600
and so is Mr. Ding.

186
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,580
We're all here.

187
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:04,080
I think Xiaoman probably

188
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,280
doesn't want too many people to know it.

189
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:08,870
Let him recover on his own.

190
00:11:08,870 --> 00:11:09,960
Give him some time.

191
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:11,200
Well,

192
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:12,800
okay then.

193
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:14,950
Let me know if anything happens.

194
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,160
Especially his medical bill.

195
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:18,320
I can pay it.

196
00:11:19,150 --> 00:11:20,000
Okay, okay.

197
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,270
I'm calling you

198
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,430
mainly because seeing Xiaoman
in that state

199
00:11:23,430 --> 00:11:24,860
made me worry about you.

200
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,510
You work so hard now,

201
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:29,150
and you're under so much pressure.

202
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:31,630
Your health is what matters most.
Do you hear me?

203
00:11:31,630 --> 00:11:32,890
Take care of yourself!

204
00:11:32,910 --> 00:11:34,310
Don't burn yourself out.

205
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:36,510
I know.

206
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:40,720
Let's clap our hands.

207
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:44,480
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

208
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:45,790
Chunchun, you're here again.

209
00:11:45,790 --> 00:11:47,600
-Hello.
-Stretching exercises. Follow me.

210
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,750
Five, six, seven, eight.

211
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:53,630
Three, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

212
00:11:53,910 --> 00:11:58,150
Four, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

213
00:11:58,150 --> 00:12:02,030
Five, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

214
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:05,870
Six, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

215
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:10,150
Seven, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

216
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:14,200
Eight, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

217
00:12:21,290 --> 00:12:22,870
Take it slow. Be careful.

218
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:24,820
Xiuxiu.

219
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:27,600
Can I take Zhang Xiaoman for a bit?

220
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:29,060
I'll bring him back later.

221
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,850
Okay. You guys be careful then.

222
00:12:30,870 --> 00:12:31,730
Zhang Xiaoman.

223
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:32,630
Xiaoman.

224
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:44,360
Why are you here?

225
00:12:46,550 --> 00:12:48,010
After returning to China,

226
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:51,000
I wasn't in a good state.

227
00:12:52,460 --> 00:12:55,590
Since I wasn't doing well, I came here

228
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:57,940
to recuperate.

229
00:13:01,870 --> 00:13:03,320
And why are you here?

230
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:08,240
I'm here as a volunteer,

231
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,440
unlike you.

232
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:19,960
When I first got back,

233
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:22,030
I went to the old dance hall.

234
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:24,450
I wanted to take a look around.

235
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,130
But when I got there,

236
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,020
it had long since closed down.

237
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:32,700
Even the shed was torn down.

238
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,440
But when I was sitting there that day...

239
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:39,670
I saw you.

240
00:13:40,710 --> 00:13:42,440
I saw you roller skating there.

241
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,680
I might have been really sick back then,

242
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:54,920
having visual hallucinations.

243
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,840
I usually don't hallucinate like that.

244
00:13:57,840 --> 00:14:00,600
I just have auditory hallucinations.

245
00:14:00,870 --> 00:14:02,630
Something's wrong with my ears.

246
00:14:02,630 --> 00:14:04,150
I hear a lot of random noises.

247
00:14:04,150 --> 00:14:06,310
Like voices talking to me,

248
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:08,110
beguiling me, or scaring me.

249
00:14:09,150 --> 00:14:10,550
I can't tell what's real.

250
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,930
I don't... don't have any other problems.

251
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:18,720
Are you feeling better now?

252
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,840
The auditory hallucinations still exist.

253
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:24,440
But f-for a while now,

254
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:27,170
I think I haven't had
any visual hallucinations.

255
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:30,120
It's okay. Don't worry.

256
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:33,380
Just take your medicine properly,

257
00:14:33,380 --> 00:14:35,110
and you'll be discharged soon.

258
00:14:36,150 --> 00:14:38,030
Why did the dance hall close down?

259
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,870
After you left,

260
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:46,590
our plant's performance
started going downhill.

261
00:14:46,790 --> 00:14:48,790
Fewer people came to the dance hall.

262
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:52,160
You know Da. He never makes money
against his conscience.

263
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:55,510
He even subsidized it with his own money,
again and again.

264
00:14:55,510 --> 00:14:57,720
In the end,
we couldn't keep it going anymore,

265
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:58,850
so we closed it down.

266
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:01,020
And we all split up.

267
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,780
Look at how things turned out.

268
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:06,120
Why did I insist on going out

269
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:08,920
to go through all that trouble?
What was the point?

270
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,080
Wouldn't it have been fine
for me to just stay home?

271
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,480
Business at the dance hall was good.

272
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,000
My little clothing stall was
doing well, too.

273
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,200
Why on earth did I insist on running off?

274
00:15:22,670 --> 00:15:24,080
You're overthinking it.

275
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:28,390
Whether you ran or not,
it'd end up the same.

276
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:34,240
You said...
You said you're volunteering here.

277
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:37,320
If you... If you don't have a real job,

278
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,240
how do you make a living?

279
00:15:40,030 --> 00:15:43,430
Do you remember that thing
when we were back at the dance hall?

280
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,840
One day, you asked me,

281
00:15:45,630 --> 00:15:50,670
"What exactly do you want to do
with all that money you earn?"

282
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,260
Does it ring a bell?

283
00:15:58,240 --> 00:15:59,200
I'm recalling.

284
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,460
Later, I saved up money

285
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:07,760
and opened a flower shop.

286
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,400
A flower shop is nice.

287
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,630
So n-now,

288
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:18,280
is the flower shop business...
running well here?

289
00:16:18,790 --> 00:16:20,650
My business is doing pretty well.

290
00:16:21,870 --> 00:16:22,840
Nowadays,

291
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:25,000
besides the holidays,

292
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:28,180
there are plenty of customers
on regular days, too.

293
00:16:28,270 --> 00:16:29,730
So business is quite good.

294
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,550
I'm glad to hear that.

295
00:16:34,550 --> 00:16:36,150
That's one piece of good news

296
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,720
I've heard since I came back.

297
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:41,320
Having your own livelihood.

298
00:16:41,790 --> 00:16:44,080
A flower shop is pretty nice. Keep at it.

299
00:16:45,390 --> 00:16:46,590
Don't cause trouble.

300
00:16:47,570 --> 00:16:49,120
We're not kids anymore.

301
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:51,030
D-Don't act rashly.

302
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:53,740
Let it slide if you can.

303
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:55,550
I know.

304
00:16:58,030 --> 00:16:59,630
I have some good news for you.

305
00:17:00,030 --> 00:17:01,490
I'm also coming on Friday.

306
00:17:02,150 --> 00:17:03,350
Do you need anything?

307
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:08,000
What I need...

308
00:17:13,069 --> 00:17:14,730
Bring me a pair of headphones.

309
00:17:15,550 --> 00:17:17,069
I'll put them on.

310
00:17:17,349 --> 00:17:18,000
Once they're on,

311
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,720
any noise will be fake.

312
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:20,880
Okay.

313
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:24,280
I'll bring you headphones.

314
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:29,300
I have to go back since the bell rings.

315
00:18:26,110 --> 00:18:27,070
That's perfect.

316
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,000
Great.

317
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,350
-Good morning.
-Chunchun, welcome.

318
00:18:30,350 --> 00:18:32,880
Look at you.
You're getting prettier every day.

319
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:33,720
I'm delivering flowers today.

320
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:34,550
So I dressed up a bit.

321
00:18:34,550 --> 00:18:35,350
That's great.

322
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:37,000
They'll be happy today.

323
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:39,880
Come on.

324
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:41,640
Alright.

325
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:42,790
Go ahead.

326
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:44,110
I'll go find Xiaoman then.

327
00:18:44,110 --> 00:18:45,720
Thanks for your hard work today.

328
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:47,040
Chunchun, don't overwork yourself.

329
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:47,440
Bye-bye.

330
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:47,970
Bye-bye.

331
00:18:54,070 --> 00:18:55,130
What are you doing?

332
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,210
It's Friday?

333
00:19:03,350 --> 00:19:04,410
Fridays are great.

334
00:19:04,590 --> 00:19:05,990
How have you been lately?

335
00:19:06,790 --> 00:19:07,440
Lately?

336
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,860
I've just been here
listening to the wind every day.

337
00:19:13,790 --> 00:19:14,520
Headphones.

338
00:19:18,950 --> 00:19:20,080
These are great.

339
00:19:20,830 --> 00:19:21,400
Thanks.

340
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,750
With these,
I don't have to keep using them.

341
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:24,760
They always fall off.

342
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:25,240
Look how much

343
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,510
I've collected in one day.
They keep falling.

344
00:19:26,510 --> 00:19:27,510
And there's more.

345
00:19:28,590 --> 00:19:30,160
I bought you an MP3.

346
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:33,000
An MP3?

347
00:19:33,060 --> 00:19:33,590
Yeah.

348
00:19:35,030 --> 00:19:36,430
It can record audio, too.

349
00:19:36,510 --> 00:19:38,440
I've downloaded
quite a few songs on it for you.

350
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:39,440
Plug it in and try.

351
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:40,160
Thanks.

352
00:19:40,270 --> 00:19:40,930
No worries.

353
00:19:46,830 --> 00:19:49,150
Great. They stay on.

354
00:19:50,660 --> 00:19:51,460
By the way,

355
00:19:53,270 --> 00:19:55,800
how much is it?
I'll pay you back when I get out.

356
00:19:55,940 --> 00:19:57,070
Don't bring up the price.

357
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:58,550
We don't talk about money.

358
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,660
I'm going somewhere else now.

359
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,010
Here's a flower for you.

360
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:04,980
I have a whole bunch,

361
00:20:04,980 --> 00:20:06,780
and I'm giving you the first one.

362
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:12,080
So I should take care of this?

363
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,680
Okay. I'll take good care of it.

364
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,550
Enjoy your music. I'm taking my leave.

365
00:20:16,550 --> 00:20:17,510
Where are you going?

366
00:20:17,510 --> 00:20:19,170
I have to give these to others.

367
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:20,680
Okay.

368
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,030
Bye.

369
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:24,470
When will you come again?

370
00:20:24,750 --> 00:20:26,210
When do you want me to come?

371
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:31,120
The day after tomorrow?

372
00:20:32,270 --> 00:20:33,510
That depends on my mood.

373
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:34,160
Bye-bye.

374
00:20:40,110 --> 00:20:41,370
Here. A flower for you.

375
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:42,840
You seem much better now.

376
00:20:43,130 --> 00:20:44,130
-Bye.
-Thank you.

377
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:45,880
Thanks.

378
00:20:47,110 --> 00:20:48,240
Here's your flower.

379
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:49,710
-Take it.
-Where's mine?

380
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,440
I'm telling you to arrange it

381
00:21:40,510 --> 00:21:42,110
when you're free. Right?

382
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:43,750
-Come to Shanghai for a few days.
-Time to eat.

383
00:21:43,750 --> 00:21:44,480
Time to eat.

384
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:46,400
Yeah.

385
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:47,810
I have enough rooms.

386
00:21:48,030 --> 00:21:49,230
My place is quite big.

387
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:52,030
Right? If needed,
we can sleep on the floor.

388
00:21:52,270 --> 00:21:53,200
We can...

389
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:54,440
Yeah.

390
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:55,880
It's mainly to get together,

391
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,350
have a few drinks, and catch up.

392
00:21:57,350 --> 00:21:58,240
I'm so bored here, too.

393
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:58,960
Come on,

394
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,400
let's eat.

395
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:02,750
I-Is that alright?

396
00:22:03,190 --> 00:22:04,520
Yeah. You make a plan.

397
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:06,050
Discuss it with your wife.

398
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:08,750
Okay, okay.

399
00:22:10,030 --> 00:22:10,890
I'm hanging up.

400
00:22:11,590 --> 00:22:12,650
Why did you rush me?

401
00:22:13,070 --> 00:22:15,350
You're making
long-distance calls like this every day,

402
00:22:15,350 --> 00:22:16,400
all the way to the Northeast,

403
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:17,530
chatting for hours.

404
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:18,440
Do you know

405
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,310
how much the monthly telephone bill is?

406
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:22,240
You don't care about these things.

407
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,350
It's so boring
to just sit around like this every day.

408
00:22:26,350 --> 00:22:27,880
I can only have a good time

409
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:30,030
by shooting the breeze with them.

410
00:22:30,030 --> 00:22:32,590
That's exactly what retirement is like.

411
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:34,790
But look at these guys.

412
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:36,480
I invite them to Shanghai for a visit.

413
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,440
I'd take them

414
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:38,830
to tour the Huangpu River.

415
00:22:38,830 --> 00:22:39,200
Right?

416
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,750
Walk along Nanjing Road.
How great it'd be!

417
00:22:40,750 --> 00:22:41,830
But no one's coming.

418
00:22:41,830 --> 00:22:43,160
I won't mention Zhuang.

419
00:22:43,470 --> 00:22:45,400
He has high blood pressure, right?

420
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:46,640
He doesn't dare travel far.

421
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:47,920
What is Ding busy with?

422
00:22:48,110 --> 00:22:49,570
He doesn't even have kids!

423
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:50,680
Whenever I call him,

424
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:52,030
he always has some excuse.

425
00:22:52,030 --> 00:22:54,510
Well, people have
their own things to handle,

426
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:55,400
don't they?

427
00:22:58,550 --> 00:22:59,270
Oh, Zhao!

428
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,030
Zhao is free.

429
00:23:02,030 --> 00:23:03,270
I'll call him.

430
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:05,030
Which Zhao?

431
00:23:05,030 --> 00:23:05,830
Zhao Cun.

432
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:08,310
Zhuang's senior.

433
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:10,920
Yan.

434
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:13,920
Zhao Cun is gone.

435
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,800
-Zhao Cun...
-He's gone.

436
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:20,920
Gone?

437
00:23:21,750 --> 00:23:22,950
When did that happen?

438
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:24,880
A long time ago.

439
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:35,530
I think I have
a vague memory of this thing.

440
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:37,590
Try to recall.

441
00:23:39,070 --> 00:23:39,960
Zhao Cun?

442
00:23:46,780 --> 00:23:48,390
How could I forget?

443
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:52,790
How did he pass away?

444
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:55,590
Zhao Cun is gone?

445
00:23:59,070 --> 00:24:01,130
I think I remember this only vaguely.

446
00:24:02,690 --> 00:24:04,580
When did it happen?

447
00:24:13,070 --> 00:24:14,070
I never thought

448
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:17,480
we'd be walking
around the campus together again.

449
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,440
You didn't expect I'd come back
to Shanghai, right?

450
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:22,030
You've been back in Shanghai
for quite a while,

451
00:24:22,030 --> 00:24:23,560
yet you didn't even tell me.

452
00:24:23,590 --> 00:24:25,310
I've been busy looking for a job.

453
00:24:25,310 --> 00:24:27,040
I didn't have time to reach out.

454
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:29,800
Your factory went under?

455
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:32,460
It's completely gone.

456
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:36,210
Everyone left was merged
into a factory in Xi'an.

457
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:38,320
Do you regret it?

458
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,270
No, I don't.

459
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:43,550
Although you told me back then

460
00:24:43,550 --> 00:24:44,400
that one person alone

461
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,400
could hardly change the factory's fate,

462
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:48,270
if I hadn't gone back to give it a shot,

463
00:24:48,270 --> 00:24:49,730
I would have regretted it.

464
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:01,480
My parents built the factory.

465
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:05,960
Now that it's gone,
they're taking it harder than I am.

466
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:06,960
I understand.

467
00:25:08,110 --> 00:25:09,030
I totally get it.

468
00:25:09,030 --> 00:25:10,960
Never mind. Let's skip this topic.

469
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,860
How have you been?
Look at you, all suited up.

470
00:25:15,270 --> 00:25:16,750
My company went bust, too.

471
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:21,070
I'm in investment banking now,

472
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,680
working as an investment manager.

473
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,070
Investment banking is nice.

474
00:25:24,070 --> 00:25:25,440
No wonder Fan Weijie was always sticking

475
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:26,750
with you back in school.

476
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:28,010
He saw your potential.

477
00:25:28,240 --> 00:25:30,100
What about you? What do you do now?

478
00:25:31,030 --> 00:25:33,430
Competition in Shanghai is way too fierce.

479
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:34,480
I looked for 2 months

480
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:36,550
and only found a job selling e-vehicles.

481
00:25:36,550 --> 00:25:38,750
I'll just do it for now, just to survive.

482
00:25:39,550 --> 00:25:41,550
Don't make it sound so miserable.

483
00:25:42,270 --> 00:25:44,720
E-vehicles are supposed to sell well.

484
00:25:45,070 --> 00:25:48,200
With your capability,
you should be earning quite a lot.

485
00:25:48,830 --> 00:25:50,270
I don't even want to talk about it.

486
00:25:50,270 --> 00:25:51,440
I do make decent money

487
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:54,030
at the cost of being a doormat
to people all the time.

488
00:25:54,030 --> 00:25:55,590
You know, these e-vehicles are

489
00:25:55,590 --> 00:25:56,650
great in every way.

490
00:25:57,310 --> 00:25:59,070
But what's
with this lithium battery technology?

491
00:25:59,070 --> 00:26:01,240
It can handle
neither the cold nor the heat well,

492
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:02,960
and overcharging is a problem as well.

493
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:06,030
The complaints about lithium batteries are
enough to make my head ache.

494
00:26:06,030 --> 00:26:07,400
Can you tell me more details

495
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:09,160
about this lithium battery technology?

496
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:09,750
Wait,

497
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:13,220
you investment bankers
really jump at every opportunity?

498
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:16,540
It's a bit of an occupational quirk
of mine.

499
00:26:17,350 --> 00:26:18,030
How about this?

500
00:26:18,030 --> 00:26:20,030
Treat me to a meal, and I'll tell you.

501
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:22,060
Deal! What do you want to eat?

502
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:23,110
The canteen food.

503
00:26:23,110 --> 00:26:24,550
Okay. Which dishes
do you want at the canteen?

504
00:26:24,550 --> 00:26:26,590
The pork chops.
I've been craving them for quite a while.

505
00:26:26,590 --> 00:26:28,720
Alright, I'll treat you to ten of them.

506
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:09,880
Zhang Xiaoman, stop right there!

507
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:10,810
You little brat!

508
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,600
I'll kick your ass!

509
00:28:53,510 --> 00:28:53,960
Hello?

510
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:54,680
Hello, Mom.

511
00:28:55,070 --> 00:28:56,730
I have some good news to share.

512
00:28:57,750 --> 00:28:59,200
One of my design concepts was

513
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:02,130
displayed
at an architecture exhibition in Europe.

514
00:29:02,790 --> 00:29:04,960
Our Sweetie is so amazing!

515
00:29:05,550 --> 00:29:07,000
I'm so happy for you.

516
00:29:07,340 --> 00:29:07,930
By the way,

517
00:29:07,930 --> 00:29:09,730
how have you and Dad been lately?

518
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,160
We're doing great.

519
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,440
Everything's good.

520
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,640
Don't worry about us.

521
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:17,790
Sweetie, can I ask you something?

522
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:18,880
Well,

523
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,510
do they have that kind

524
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:24,240
of medicine for Alzheimer's abroad?

525
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,830
Alzheimer's?

526
00:29:26,010 --> 00:29:27,140
Who needs to take it?

527
00:29:27,830 --> 00:29:29,680
An old colleague of your dad's.

528
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:32,480
He knows you're abroad

529
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:34,010
and wants us to ask you.

530
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:38,490
Okay, I got it.
I'll help you ask around later.

531
00:29:38,750 --> 00:29:39,720
As long as it's not about you two.

532
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:40,960
You two must go to the hospital

533
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:42,000
when feeling unwell.

534
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,240
Okay, okay. We know.

535
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,240
We know when to go to the hospital.

536
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:45,160
No worries.

537
00:29:45,830 --> 00:29:47,100
I'm heading to work now.

538
00:29:47,100 --> 00:29:48,360
I'll hang up. Bye-bye.

539
00:30:07,790 --> 00:30:09,440
Chunchun. Chunchun.

540
00:30:09,790 --> 00:30:11,250
Come here. Help me with it.

541
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:29,880
Chunchun,

542
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:31,530
look at these flowers.

543
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:33,360
Their roots are rotting.

544
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:36,050
We have to leave an air hole in the soil.

545
00:30:36,310 --> 00:30:37,750
Leave a gap for air,

546
00:30:38,110 --> 00:30:39,590
so the light can shine in.

547
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:49,680
Chunchun,

548
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:52,300
I'm leaving the wind chime to you.

549
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:54,160
When the wind chime rings,

550
00:30:54,550 --> 00:30:56,920
it's me turning into the wind
to visit you.

551
00:30:57,960 --> 00:30:59,110
It's me missing you.

552
00:31:03,030 --> 00:31:04,160
Why are you here?

553
00:31:05,970 --> 00:31:07,170
What brings you here?

554
00:31:11,750 --> 00:31:12,400
I...

555
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:15,440
followed the sound of the chime.

556
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:17,310
Then I saw this place was pretty nice,

557
00:31:17,310 --> 00:31:19,400
so I cleared the path here.

558
00:31:22,310 --> 00:31:23,570
It sounds really nice.

559
00:31:31,350 --> 00:31:32,640
When I hear this sound,

560
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,780
I feel much calmer.

561
00:31:35,350 --> 00:31:37,750
This is a nice place.
It's just a bit shabby.

562
00:31:38,510 --> 00:31:39,720
How is it shabby?

563
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:41,310
Isn't it great enough?

564
00:31:41,310 --> 00:31:43,370
Look. There is hardly any glass left.

565
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:48,200
If it weren't broken,

566
00:31:49,750 --> 00:31:51,410
how could the sunlight get in?

567
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,480
That's true.

568
00:31:58,350 --> 00:32:00,280
Do you know what flowers those are?

569
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:02,680
Aren't they just

570
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,750
dahlias, asters, and such?

571
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:09,240
Next time you come,

572
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,960
bring me some seeds from the market.

573
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:16,540
I'll plant them with you then.

574
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:18,830
Okay.

575
00:33:00,550 --> 00:33:01,350
Xiaoman!

576
00:33:02,550 --> 00:33:03,110
Xiaoman!

577
00:33:04,030 --> 00:33:04,720
Come give me a hand!

578
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:05,440
It's stuck!

579
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:06,200
Coming.

580
00:33:06,750 --> 00:33:07,920
This is such a steep slope.

581
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:08,650
Take it slow.

582
00:33:10,080 --> 00:33:11,410
You brought a full load?

583
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:13,000
-Hello.
-I'm here to help.

584
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:14,440
One, two, go.

585
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:17,000
Okay.

586
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:17,550
Good!

587
00:33:23,350 --> 00:33:25,240
My goodness, why did you bring so much?

588
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,440
I just wanted a pickaxe, a hoe,
or something else

589
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,640
to plant some flowers.

590
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:30,370
But t-this is a whole cartload.

591
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:31,640
I didn't know how big the job was,

592
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:33,440
so I brought everything for you.

593
00:33:34,030 --> 00:33:34,680
Hello.

594
00:33:34,830 --> 00:33:35,440
Hello.

595
00:33:36,790 --> 00:33:38,590
This... This is my mentor,

596
00:33:38,590 --> 00:33:40,270
Mr. Ding. He brought me up.

597
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:42,240
This is Chunchun.

598
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:44,300
We were colleagues at the dance hall.

599
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:45,720
Now she's here to help me plant flowers.

600
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:46,650
Hello, Mr. Ding.

601
00:33:47,070 --> 00:33:47,680
Hello.

602
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:49,350
Good.

603
00:33:51,370 --> 00:33:52,350
I'll leave you two to it.

604
00:33:52,350 --> 00:33:53,640
I'm going to take the stuff.

605
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:54,680
-Um...
-Y-You don't have to do that.

606
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:55,350
It's fine.

607
00:33:55,350 --> 00:33:56,720
Just carry something small. Small items.

608
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:58,000
I can move them.

609
00:33:59,510 --> 00:34:00,240
What a pity.

610
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:03,550
She's such a young girl,

611
00:34:03,550 --> 00:34:05,070
so pretty,
yet she has this kind of disease, too.

612
00:34:05,070 --> 00:34:05,670
Oh, God...

613
00:34:05,750 --> 00:34:07,240
What are you talking about?

614
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:08,760
She's working here as a volunteer.

615
00:34:08,760 --> 00:34:09,620
She's not sick.

616
00:34:10,550 --> 00:34:12,350
My condition isn't contagious.

617
00:34:13,110 --> 00:34:14,800
Good, so she is healthy

618
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:16,070
and works so efficiently.

619
00:34:16,070 --> 00:34:17,110
She's a nice girl.

620
00:34:17,110 --> 00:34:18,840
She's good at it.
She works... works so efficiently.

621
00:34:18,840 --> 00:34:19,550
Don't bother.

622
00:34:19,550 --> 00:34:20,679
Leave it, Chunchun.

623
00:34:20,710 --> 00:34:21,840
It's okay. I can take it.

624
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:22,710
You take it, Xiaoman.

625
00:34:22,710 --> 00:34:23,230
You...

626
00:34:23,230 --> 00:34:24,110
Chunchun, leave it to me...

627
00:34:24,110 --> 00:34:24,880
You... Put it down.

628
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:25,360
It's dirty.

629
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:26,030
No, no, no.

630
00:34:26,030 --> 00:34:27,110
-You need to wear gloves.
-Listen to me.

631
00:34:27,110 --> 00:34:27,760
Give... Give that to me.

632
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:28,590
Come on. Give it to me.

633
00:34:28,590 --> 00:34:29,280
I'll carry it.

634
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:29,880
Leave it to me.

635
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:31,739
You can just give it to me. Come on.

636
00:34:32,030 --> 00:34:33,159
I'll carry it later.

637
00:34:34,230 --> 00:34:35,150
Miss, I...

638
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:39,590
He told me that you're volunteering here.

639
00:34:39,590 --> 00:34:40,920
Yes, I've been doing it for quite a while.

640
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:43,110
S-So, you've known him
for a long time, right?

641
00:34:43,110 --> 00:34:44,969
We've known each other for years.

642
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:46,480
Good.

643
00:34:47,699 --> 00:34:49,300
About Xiaoman's illness...

644
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,440
It's getting better each time.

645
00:34:52,440 --> 00:34:53,760
The doctor says he's fine.

646
00:34:53,760 --> 00:34:54,710
Plus, he's young.

647
00:34:54,710 --> 00:34:55,550
And he's strong.

648
00:34:55,550 --> 00:34:57,550
They say it won't affect his future.

649
00:34:58,070 --> 00:34:58,630
Yes.

650
00:34:58,630 --> 00:34:59,550
Everything is normal.

651
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:00,960
Could you please look after him?

652
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:02,110
Don't worry. Here in the hospital,

653
00:35:02,110 --> 00:35:03,550
I'll take good care of him.

654
00:35:03,550 --> 00:35:04,440
Okay, nice.

655
00:35:05,150 --> 00:35:06,320
Alright. I'll carry them inside.

656
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:07,000
Don't bother taking any.

657
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:07,860
I can handle them myself.

658
00:35:07,860 --> 00:35:10,920
[Tiecheng Anning Hospital]

659
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:27,280
I think this project is

660
00:35:27,510 --> 00:35:29,150
tailor-made for you.

661
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:32,590
Our company is planning to acquire
Factory No. 3 of the East Chemical Plant?

662
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:34,710
Exactly. They've restructured now.

663
00:35:35,190 --> 00:35:37,880
The state holds a stake,
and foreign capital can participate, too.

664
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,510
You're from the East Chemical Plant.

665
00:35:39,510 --> 00:35:41,920
You have both an emotional connection
and technical expertise.

666
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:44,150
You are the perfect one to lead this.

667
00:35:44,670 --> 00:35:47,670
As a civilian factory, Factory No. 3
covers a wide range of areas.

668
00:35:47,670 --> 00:35:49,440
Moreover,
the East Chemical Plant is no longer

669
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:51,710
fully state-owned
after the transformation.

670
00:35:51,710 --> 00:35:53,190
The problems involved are not fewer

671
00:35:53,190 --> 00:35:55,850
than those
at Jiangnan Machinery Plant, right?

672
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,460
So, as someone
from the East Chemical Plant,

673
00:35:59,510 --> 00:36:01,280
you should interact with them more.

674
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:03,230
No matter what cards they play later,

675
00:36:03,230 --> 00:36:04,000
for you,

676
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:07,290
isn't it like they're showing their hand?

677
00:36:07,630 --> 00:36:09,440
Then how do you see this project,
Mr. Kong?

678
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:11,590
The equity structure has changed
after the transformation.

679
00:36:11,590 --> 00:36:12,960
Whether in terms of policy

680
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:14,710
or economics,

681
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:16,070
Factory No. 3

682
00:36:16,070 --> 00:36:17,760
can't afford any more hits.

683
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:19,130
Our foreign investment

684
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:21,030
would be their lifeline.

685
00:36:21,710 --> 00:36:23,920
You just go and be their savior.

686
00:36:24,150 --> 00:36:27,150
After the divestiture,
re-evaluate the assets

687
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:30,110
and try to get it at the lowest price.

688
00:36:31,630 --> 00:36:34,590
Why are you so sure
I'll take this project?

689
00:36:37,630 --> 00:36:38,710
Because I know,

690
00:36:40,150 --> 00:36:42,210
even if Factory No. 3 is going to fall,

691
00:36:42,630 --> 00:36:46,160
you wouldn't want it to be ended
in someone else's hands, right?

692
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:52,030
Thanks.

693
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:02,920
It was the most thriving civilian factory
of the East Chemical Plant back then.

694
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:05,440
I never expected Factory No. 3 would fall

695
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,170
to the point of being acquired.

696
00:37:07,590 --> 00:37:09,320
Do you remember back in 1997,

697
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:11,510
when we played with bubbles
at the Mahavira Hall?

698
00:37:11,510 --> 00:37:12,280
At that time, I already felt

699
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:14,410
the East Chemical Plant was so unreal.

700
00:37:14,500 --> 00:37:15,900
Everything was just

701
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,780
like those shining soap bubbles,

702
00:37:18,510 --> 00:37:20,440
destined to burst sooner or later.

703
00:37:21,190 --> 00:37:23,550
After
all these state-owned enterprise reforms,

704
00:37:23,550 --> 00:37:24,950
the day has finally come.

705
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:25,960
Yeah.

706
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:28,880
I just didn't expect
that it would happen so fast.

707
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:30,080
But having said that,

708
00:37:30,590 --> 00:37:33,150
acquisition is essentially
attracting investment

709
00:37:33,150 --> 00:37:34,280
and trading property rights.

710
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:37,360
Bringing in foreign capital
to push the factory to market is

711
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:39,550
still better than letting it sit idle
and go to waste.

712
00:37:39,550 --> 00:37:40,760
It's inevitable.

713
00:37:41,670 --> 00:37:43,510
Given the current economic situation,

714
00:37:43,510 --> 00:37:46,440
if companies don't undergo
industrial transformation

715
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:47,960
or take in fresh blood,

716
00:37:48,630 --> 00:37:49,190
in view

717
00:37:49,190 --> 00:37:51,480
of their extremely fragile
economic systems,

718
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:54,140
they'll face the risk
of collapse at any moment.

719
00:37:55,510 --> 00:37:56,800
But I really didn't expect that you

720
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:58,330
would take on this project.

721
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:00,840
Even if I didn't take it,

722
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:02,920
someone else would have.

723
00:38:04,190 --> 00:38:05,800
Work is work.

724
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:07,930
I won't mix personal feelings into it.

725
00:38:08,070 --> 00:38:09,130
You taught me this.

726
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:13,400
I know you're capable.

727
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:18,010
Don't you always say I have foresight?

728
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:20,800
I don't think this issue
about Factory No. 3

729
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:23,130
can be solved just by following the rules.

730
00:38:25,710 --> 00:38:26,840
I'm worried you'll ruin

731
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:28,500
your own career because of it.

732
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:31,330
Kong Peng is obviously
taking revenge on you.

733
00:38:31,510 --> 00:38:32,750
I didn't back down

734
00:38:32,750 --> 00:38:34,010
regarding Fan Weijie.

735
00:38:34,150 --> 00:38:36,480
Kong Peng can only use work
to pressure me.

736
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:40,800
The acquisition targets the factory,
not the people.

737
00:38:42,030 --> 00:38:44,360
If it's acquired, everyone will get paid.

738
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:47,900
It's better than dying
in the "winter of the industry."

739
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:49,440
I just don't know

740
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:51,970
if the people at Factory No. 3
know about this.

741
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:55,070
Their fate was sealed long ago.

742
00:38:57,710 --> 00:39:00,510
You should think carefully
about your own future.

743
00:39:07,180 --> 00:39:07,710
It's raining.

744
00:39:07,710 --> 00:39:10,280
Hurry, let's go.

745
00:39:14,110 --> 00:39:15,370
It was such a sunny day.

746
00:39:15,510 --> 00:39:16,510
It's actually a good thing.

747
00:39:16,510 --> 00:39:19,070
God is doing the watering,
saving us the trouble.

748
00:39:19,070 --> 00:39:20,930
This rain is actually a blessing.

749
00:39:24,030 --> 00:39:25,000
Let it rain.

750
00:39:33,320 --> 00:39:35,800
Actually, this whole garden

751
00:39:36,590 --> 00:39:38,050
used to be full of flowers.

752
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:41,220
You know who planted them, right?

753
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:52,510
It's okay.

754
00:39:53,230 --> 00:39:54,960
No matter who planted them before,

755
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:55,960
now that we're here,

756
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:59,440
we'll make this greenhouse thrive.

757
00:40:00,590 --> 00:40:02,030
My mom and I planted them.

758
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:03,920
My mom

759
00:40:04,630 --> 00:40:06,440
lived in the ICU across the way

760
00:40:07,670 --> 00:40:08,720
for 3 years.

761
00:40:09,590 --> 00:40:11,390
When she was first brought here,

762
00:40:13,150 --> 00:40:15,150
everyone tied her to the bed.

763
00:40:15,510 --> 00:40:18,800
The doctor told me
she had violent tendencies.

764
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:23,230
Actually, there's a lot from my childhood

765
00:40:23,230 --> 00:40:24,360
that I can't recall.

766
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,440
But I do remember,

767
00:40:27,150 --> 00:40:28,880
after my mom ran away from home,

768
00:40:29,630 --> 00:40:31,800
my dad often beat me for no reason.

769
00:40:32,150 --> 00:40:34,150
Every time he hit me, he would say,

770
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:37,960
"Your mom is a bad woman."

771
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:41,280
"She doesn't want you anymore."

772
00:40:41,280 --> 00:40:43,480
So when I was little, I really hated her.

773
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:45,880
I hated that she didn't like me.

774
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:47,670
I hated that she didn't want me.

775
00:40:47,670 --> 00:40:49,600
I thought that was why I got beaten.

776
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:51,110
But then one day,

777
00:40:53,150 --> 00:40:55,080
she brought me to this greenhouse.

778
00:40:56,070 --> 00:40:57,150
She told me that

779
00:40:57,590 --> 00:40:59,590
when I was very, very little,

780
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:01,400
she took me away from my dad

781
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:02,800
for a period of time.

782
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:04,800
But a few years later,

783
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,670
she found out she was sick.

784
00:41:12,630 --> 00:41:14,280
She really had no choice.

785
00:41:17,740 --> 00:41:19,600
It wasn't that she didn't want me.

786
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:30,710
Let me tell you my story.

787
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:34,480
We're actually a bit alike.

788
00:41:35,230 --> 00:41:36,490
My mom also passed away

789
00:41:36,670 --> 00:41:38,030
when I was very little.

790
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:41,230
So I don't remember much about her.

791
00:41:43,550 --> 00:41:44,800
The difference is

792
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,610
that my dad also left me.

793
00:41:48,230 --> 00:41:49,290
They're both gone.

794
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:51,820
It was just me and my grandma left.

795
00:42:01,590 --> 00:42:04,530
Do you know
why there's a wind chime there?

796
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:08,830
My mom told me about it.

797
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:10,920
When I was little,

798
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:12,650
my mom raised me all by herself.

799
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:14,170
But she had to make money

800
00:42:14,710 --> 00:42:16,570
and came home very late every day.

801
00:42:17,190 --> 00:42:19,230
So she hung a wind chime at the door.

802
00:42:20,230 --> 00:42:23,670
Every time she came home
and opened the door,

803
00:42:24,770 --> 00:42:26,800
the wind chime would ring.

804
00:42:27,190 --> 00:42:30,520
I felt like there was something
to look forward to every day.

805
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:34,480
You mean it's given you a sense
of security since you were little.

806
00:42:35,590 --> 00:42:37,000
And now,

807
00:42:37,920 --> 00:42:39,070
it can help me, too.

808
00:42:50,070 --> 00:42:51,930
I'm giving this wind chime to you.

809
00:42:52,630 --> 00:42:54,160
It protected me in the past.

810
00:42:54,190 --> 00:42:55,720
Now let it protect you.
